      <div class = "col s12" id = "httpserver">
        <h3>Basic http server</h3>
      </div>
      <div class = "col s12">
        <p>NodeJS provides us with helpful modules out of the box. One of these is called http. Using http
        we can start up a server that will respond with a greeting.</p>
        <pre class = "card panel grey darken-4">
          <code>
<span class = "red-text lighten-1">var</span> http = <span class = "yellow-text lighten-1">require</span>(<span class = "green-text text-accent-3">"http"</span>);

http.createServer(<span class = "red-text lighten-1">function</span>(req, res){
  res.<span class = "yellow-text lighten-1">write</span>(<span class = "green-text text-accent-3">"Hello there!"</span>);
  res.end();
}).listen(<span class = "blue-grey-text lighten-4">3000</span>);
          </code>
        </pre>
      </div>

      <div class = "col s12" id = "httprequest">
        <h3>Basic http request</h3>
      </div>
      <div class = "aaa col s12">
        <p>We can use the http module to make requests for webpages.</p>
        <pre class = "card panel grey darken-4">
          <code>
<span class = "red-text lighten-1">var</span> http = <span class = "yellow-text lighten-1">require</span>(<span class = "green-text text-accent-3">"http"</span>);

http.request({
  host: <span class = "green-text text-accent-3">"example.com"</span>,
  path: <span class = "green-text text-accent-3">"/"</span>
}, <span class = "red-text lighten-1">function</span>(response){
  <span class = "red-text lighten-1">var</span> webpage = <span class = "green-text text-accent-3">" "</span>;
  response.on(<span class = "green-text text-accent-3">"data"</span>, <span class = "red-text lighten-1">function</span>(data){
    webpage += data;
  });
  response.on(<span class = "green-text text-accent-3">"end"</span>, <span class = "red-text lighten-1">function</span>(){
    <span class = "blue-grey-text lighten-4">console</span>.<span class = "yellow-text lighten-1">log</span>(webpage);
  });
}).end();
          </code>
        </pre>
      </div>

      <div class = "col s12" id = "httprequestimage">
        <h3>Basic image download using http request</h3>
      </div>
      <div class = "xxx col s12">
        <p>Let's use <span class = "red-text lighten-1">http.request</span> to fetch an image and then we'll use another module named <span class = "red-text lighten-1">fs</span> to save that image.</p>
        <pre class = "card panel grey darken-4">
          <code>
<span class = "red-text lighten-1">var</span> http = <span class = "yellow-text lighten-1">require</span>(<span class = "green-text text-accent-3">"http"</span>);
<span class = "red-text lighten-1">var</span> fs = <span class = "yellow-text lighten-1">require</span>(<span class = "green-text text-accent-3">"fs"</span>);

<span class = "red-text lighten-1">var</span> writeStream = fs.createWriteStream(<span class = "green-text text-accent-3">"ourImage.jpg"</span>);

http.request({
  host: <span class = "green-text text-accent-3">"i.imgur.com"</span>,
  path: <span class = "green-text text-accent-3">"/gmRbksB.jpg"</span>
}, <span class = "red-text lighten-1">function</span>(response){
  response.on(<span class = "green-text text-accent-3">"data"</span>, <span class = "red-text lighten-1">function</span>(data){
    writeStream.<span class = "yellow-text lighten-1">write</span>(data);
  });
}).end();
          </code>
        </pre>
      </div>

      <div class = "col s12" id = "httpresponsehtml">
        <h3>Serving html with your server</h3>
      </div>
      <div class = "yyy col s12">
        <p>Here we'll create a readable stream that pipes everything out into the response. Make sure to create an index.html file where this file is located.</p>
        <pre class = "card panel grey darken-4">
          <code>
<span class = "red-text lighten-1">var</span> http = <span class = "yellow-text lighten-1">require</span>(<span class = "green-text text-accent-3">"http"</span>);
<span class = "red-text lighten-1">var</span> fs = <span class = "yellow-text lighten-1">require</span>(<span class = "green-text text-accent-3">"fs"</span>);

http.createServer(<span class = "red-text lighten-1">function</span>(req, res){
    <span class = "red-text lighten-1">var</span> html = fs.createReadStream(<span class = "green-text text-accent-3">"index.html"</span>);
    html.pipe(res);
    html.on(<span class = "green-text text-accent-3">"end"</span>, <span class = "red-text lighten-1">function</span>(){
      res.end();
    });
}).listen(<span class = "blue-grey-text lighten-4">4000</span>);


          </code>
        </pre>
